# In short

- Want to reuse a Sanctum doc page or illustration? CC-BY-4.0 — credit Sanctum.
- Want to lift the Astro config or a component? Apache-2.0 — keep the copyright header.
- Building a competing product on Sanctum's playbook? Allowed by both
  licenses, but please credit the source per CC-BY-4.0 attribution.

Note: code-bearing repositories under the Sanctum project (sanctum-cli,
sanctum-mlx-fast, sanctum-rs, etc.) are licensed under FSL-1.1-Apache-2.0
(Functional Source License, Apache 2.0 Future) which adds a 2-year
anti-SaaS-competition clause that automatically converts to plain
Apache-2.0. Docs and consumer-facing content (this repo + sanctum.haus)
are under the more permissive licenses above.
